        <body>
            <div type="bibliography">
                <listRelation>
                    <relation name="ecrm:P129_is_about" active="LIT6593Poem" passive="PRS6006Kiros"><desc>Though Kiros is not mentioned in the poem, 
                    its inclusion in his hagiographic dossier and the attribute <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፈታሔ፡ ማኅፀን፡</foreign> normally referring to him
                    make him the likely subject of the poem.</desc></relation>
                    <relation name="ecrm:P129_is_about" active="LIT6593Poem" passive="PRS8083Raphael"><desc>St Raphael is mentioned in both stanzas and might
                    be the subject of the second stanza.</desc></relation>
                </listRelation>
            </div>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="stanza" xml:id="Stanza1" xml:lang="gez">
                    <note>The following stanza is taken from <ref type="mss" corresp="ESdmd013"/> .</note>
                    <ab>ነዓ፡ ኀቤየ፡ እንዘ፡ ታተሉ፡ ሊቃናተ፨ ከመ፡
                        ትፈጽም፡ ኵሎ፡ ዘልቡናየ፡ ተምኔተ፨ ቅዱስ፡ ሩፋኤል፡ እንተ፡ ትስዕል፡ ምሕረተ፨ ለሰብዕ፡ ወለዕንስሳ፡ ፈታሔ፡
                        ማኅጸኖሙ፡ አንተ፨ ወጸላሎትከ፡ ያነሥእ፡ ዘሞተ፨</ab>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="stanza" xml:id="Stanza2" xml:lang="gez">
                    <note>The following stanza is taken from <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient567"/> .</note>
                    <ab>
                        ሰላም፡ ለተፈጥሮትከ፡ ምስለ፡ እንስሳ፡ ፬ቱ። 
                        ዘከመ፡ እፎ፡ ውእቱ። 
                        ናዛዜ፡ ኅዙናን፡ ሩፋኤል፡ ገሃደ፡ ለለዕለቱ።
                        በሎሙ፡ በእንቲአየ፡ ለአብያጺከ፡ ፮ቱ
                        ። ፍቁረ፡ ዚአየ፡ ነዋ፡ አፍቅርዎ፡ ሎቱ።
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
